RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 93. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 24000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HONEYMOON SUITE sped clear early and crossed over, cut the corner into the stretch, drifted out through the lane and held well. LEMON DROP SHOT chased four outside a rival into the turn, spun three wide into the lane, moved out in the lane and finished willingly to close the gap on the winner. CARPE BELLUM chased in range early while moved off the inside, went three then two wide around the bend, kept on through the lane and outfinished HULK for third. HULK paused early then switch outside the leader while closest in pursuit, ridden along in the two path on the turn, flattened in the final furlong and lost the show. AGAPETOS was off a bit slow and dropped back, round the bend in the two path and improved position while failing to threaten. COLLEGE BOY chased between rivals early then got crowded and shuffled back near the half-mile pole, angled in to save ground through the turn and failed to menace. TUCKER'S TRIBUTE sat off the pace outside rivals early, angled in then back out on the turn, lacked further response in the drive, pulled up on the clubhouse turn and walked into the van. RAVELLO chased wide up the backstretch, went five then four wide while falling back on the turn and had little left for the stretch run.

ENTRY.NAME: Carpe Bellum
ENTRY.OWNER: Aldabbagh Omar Comestro Rob Haymes Neil A and Koriner Brian

ENTRY.NAME: College Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased between, crowded 1/2, inside, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Hulk
ENTRY.COMMENT: paused early, switched out, closest 2wide, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Tucker's Tribute
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, angled in/out turn, no response, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Honeymoon Suite
ENTRY.COMMENT: cleared, crossed over, inside, drifted out str, held well

ENTRY.NAME: Ravello
ENTRY.OWNER: Rancho Ravello LLC and Sackett Tamara C

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 78. Waiver Claiming Purse 24000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TROPICANA GIRL stalked from outside up the backstretch, rounded the bend three wide, drew alongside the leader with a furlong remaining and dug in to edge away late. BELLA RENELLA broke out a bit then went up to stalk the pace along the inside, cut the corner into the stretch, looked to make a run up the rail but lacked room behind RAIN DIVA, steered off the fence and finished determinedly to edge that rival for second. RAIN DIVA vied with TROPICANA GIRL briefly before taking full control, showed the way in the two path around the bend, met the challenge from the winner with a furlong left to run, resisted to the sixteenth pole, then yielded late and was nailed for second. FLATTERWITHJEWELS settled off the pace, angled into the two path, moved out in the drive and failed to threaten. SAILING ALONG got put in tight between rivals and checked shortly after the start, came out at the half-mile pole, took the turn four then five wide and never made an impact. RIGHTEOUSLY was rank briefly early, tracked in the four path through the turn and faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Bella Renella
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out bit, stalked inside, tight 1/8, altered out, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Righteously
ENTRY.OWNER: KW Racing LLC and Miller David J

ENTRY.NAME: Sailing Along
ENTRY.COMMENT: tight/checked start, came out 1/2, 4-5wide, no impact

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 100. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 72000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Clai ming, Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $16,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts Preferred)(Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TALKLESSWORKMORE sped to the front and moved inside, was pressured by SO I'M TOLD early before moving clear on the backstretch, challenged by that rival on the far turn, shook free under hand urging in upper stretch, put to the crop shortly after and drew off. SO I'M TOLD applied pressure to the leader early from outside then remained close up the backstretch, drew alongside once again on the far turn, could not kick on with the winner at three-sixteenths pole and stayed on to secure the place. LIL RICHARDS BELLO angled over to the rail into the first turn while giving chase then came out leaving that bend, took aim three wide into the stretch but flattened in the lane. NOLONGERAHOBBY chased along the rail then pause behind a rival entering the first turn, switched out into the two path, went four wide into the far turn, dropped back while moving into the three path around the bend and came up empty in the lane. BOTTLE OF SMOKE was off slow from the outside, took the first turn three then four wide, continued at the back in the middle stages, remained off the rail and came three wide into the stretch and never got involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Richards Bello
ENTRY.OWNER: Ciaglia Racing LLC and SAF Racing

ENTRY.NAME: Talklessworkmore
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, inside, met bid, kicked clear

ENTRY.NAME: So I'm Told
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close outside, bid outside 2nd, no match late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BONITA LEONA chased along the rail into the first turn, steadied behind the leader then moved off the inside around the bend, tugged the rider forward to draw alongside and dueled up the backstretch, took over and cleared around the far turn, showed the way two wide into the stretch inched away under a drive. ROMAN EMPRESS was prominent early between rivals then got put in tight nearing the first turn, chased four then five wide around the bend, angled in early on the backstretch, split foes early on the far turn, went two to three wide into the stretch and got up for second. TROJAN WAY hustled to the front and took control early, went four wide into the first turn then crossed over to the rail, dueled inside BONITA LENOA up the backstretch, lost contact with that rival past the five-sixteenths pole, kept on from the fence in the drive and got outfinished for second. STARSHIP SKY broke a step slow, chased on the inside then steadied behind the winner on the first turn, lost ground through the far turn while along the fence, moved out in the drive and kept on for a minor award. CALIFORNIA GIGI broke on top then became rank while three then four wide on the turn, trailed four wide on the second bend and lacked a rally. SPRING SPINNING stalked two then three wide on the first turn, continued three wide into the stretch and never responded to urging.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DESERVEDLY took control from inside, met the challenge from FAMOUS STAR on the turn, put away that rival in upper stretch and held safely under a drive. PURIFIED broke inward to lose a step at the start, tracked off the inside, went between rivals on the turn then asked right-handed two wide at the quarter pole, finished willingly in the final furlong but could not get to the winner. WARRIOR ROAD chased four deep into the turn, three deep into the stretch and flattened in the furlong grounds. FAMOUS STAR raced up close between rivals early, challenged DESERVEDLY around the turn, lost touch with that rival in upper stretch and weakened. CUPID'S CRUSADER broke in and brushed rival at the start, chased along the rail into the turn, moved out in the lane and lacked a rally. LUTHER PASS chased three deep into the turn, lost ground three wide around the bend and weakened down the lane. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Irish O'Brien S. SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 97. Stakes Purse 100000. DOWNHILL TURF FOR GOLDEN STATE SERIES ELIGIBLE CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, March 9, 2023, closed with 16 or by Supplementary nomination of $25 ,000 due at time of entry for Non Golden State Series eligible horses or $2,000 for Golden State Series eligible horses. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to Start with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to t hird, $6,000 to fourth, and $2,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of Two races other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALICE MARBLE was closest in pursuit to the outside of the pacesetter early, applied pressure into the turn, vied between foes and took over with a quarter mile left to run, inched ahead in upper stretch and held ROSE MADDOX at bay in deep stretch. ROSE MADDOX broke a step slow and trailed early then angled to the inside and moved into stalking position behind the leader, tried to launch a bid at the five-sixteenths pole but lacked room and checked hard, swung four wide leaving the bend, finished gamely from outside but lacked the needed late punch. TAMING THE TIGRESS stalked outside rivals to the turn, challenged three deep around the bend, could not keep up with ALICE MARBLE into the final furlong and flattened to third. FEELING GRAZEFUL showed speed from inside to assume command, vied with outside pair around the bend, relinquished the lead at the quarter pole and weakened down the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOUL OF MIDNIGHT cleared early, showed the way up the backstretch, led two wide then along the inside into the stretch, asked right-handed in upper stretch and widened through the final furlong. GLASS BEACH chased three wide into the turn, remained off the rail to the stretch and bested the rest. BUCK OWENS turned his head and broke slow, advanced four then three wide outside rivals on the turn, summoned a mild rally and gained the show honors. BIG DRINKER broke a step slow, traveled near mid-pack early, came six wide into the drive and could not rally. CHAOKOON got bumped leaving the gate, settled off the pace, angled in on the turn, moved out in the drive and failed to threaten. LE VRON JAMES bumped with CHAOKOON leaving the gate, lost his path early, angled in then back out on the turn, spun five wide into the lane, got put in tight between runners at the eighth pole and could not rally after. WE NEED MARKETING hopped and brushed the gate, raced in range up the backstretch, traveled wide around the bend and faded. R HEART OF GOLD lost his path and steadied early, ran up on heels on the backstretch, got boxed in on the turn and weakened. LUCKY SAM sat off the pace, traveled three wide then got floated out at the quarter pole, came five wide into the drive and failed to menace. SMUGGLER'S COVE brushed at the start, got crowded a bit between rivals early, lost ground leaving the backstretch, dropped back around the turn and tired. ANOTHER STRIKE chased between rivals nearing the turn and got shuffled back into the bend, dropped back and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TECUMSEH CAROLINE broke out, stalked in the two path, loomed three deep on the far turn, took over at the eighth pole and gamely prevailed. ROSE HARBOR was off slow and bumped at the start, raced off the pace then moved closer on the backstretch, had to pause when running up behind a rival near the half-mile pole, came three wide into the stretch, rallied four deep in the final sixteenth and just missed. RACE.FOOTNOTES: PIROLI bumped leaving the gate, tracked three wide early, inched closer outside rivals in the middle stages, bid three deep on the final bend, took over and drew clear in upper stretch, then held over the late run from FINNEUS in the final sixteenth. FINNEUS became rank nearing the first turn, stalked two wide then went between rivals on the backstretch, lacked room behind the leaders entering the stretch, tipped out and finished gamely inside the winner but could not get by. STREET RUCKUS stalked along the fence, got blocked behind troubled rival early on the far turn, tipped out to split foes then came four wide into the drive and lacked a rally. GOT THUNDER vied three deep into the first turn, dueled from outside up the backstretch, fought two wide then between rivals into the lane and weakened. BLETCHLEY PARK vied two wide inside a pair of rivals into the first turn, was coaxed along to stay up with outside pair in the middle stages, got shuffled along the fence into the far turn and faded. CARSON JEN vied three wide then cleared early, got pressured by WINDOW SHOPPING on the backstretch, dueled with that rival into the far turn, lost command at the three-eighths pole, could not keep pace past the five-sixteenths pole and weakened in the final furlong. FOOLISH vied four deep into the first turn while bumping with IRISH PATSY, chased five wide into the backstretch, moved inward and took the second turn two wide and came up empty. BEST YEAR EVER got brushed leaving the gate, took the first turn three then four wide, saved ground on the far turn and also came up empty.
